    <abstract id="aspace_3da70d78e4f6bdeb64059ec837d2313f">Upon his father's death in 1889, M. Stanford Jackson took over the daily operations and management of the Idlewood Hotel and Cottages (formerly the Jackson family's Greenwood home). This collection consists of correspondence to M. Stanford Jackson, receipts and one ledger possibly in connection the Idlewood Hotel. Several souvenirs/advertising brochures for the Idlewood, as well as calling cards, birth announcements, daily menu plans and other miscellaneous items are also present.</abstract>
